Event: PHEAA Virtual Financial Aid Presentation

Event Date: September 19, 2020
Event Time: 9:00 AM to 10:30 AM

Event Duration: 1-1/2 hours

Description: Join PHEAA for a Virtual Financial Aid Presentation Webinar from the comfort of your home! This presentation provides an early understanding of the financial decisions students need to make concerning higher education. I will discuss higher education costs, the types of financial aid available, and how to apply for financial aid. Participants will have the opportunity to enter questions in the Q & A section at any time, as well as at the end of the presentation.

post_text:
Check out this EXCITING NEWS!!!

Effective Tuesday, September 8th, all SELSD students will not be charged for breakfast or lunch. All students may still be able to purchase second meals and 5th -12th grade students may purchase ala carte items providing they have available funds in their cafeteria account. This change is in response to the federal government extending the Seamless Summer Option Program. This program will remain in effect until December 31, 2020 or until we are notified by the federal government. We will also be offering this to our virtual students soon. Stay tuned. If you have any questions, please call in to the school offices.

post_text:
We worked further today with the Department of Health. Their evaluation of the situation is that no one at the school, students or staff met the criteria for exposure, per their guidelines. According to the Department of Health, exposure is defined by being within 6 feet of a COVID positive person, for at least 15 minutes, without proper protection, within the 48 hour period, prior to the onset of that person’s symptoms and continuing until that person is symptom free. (Fever free for 24 hours without fever reducing medicine and lessening of symptoms.)
School will resume tomorrow, September 3, 2020. We had a very good first two days and we are looking forward to finishing the week on a strong note. I would like to thank our educational community for their understanding and continued support.

Joe Renzi

post_text:
Good evening.

This is to inform you that we were notified today that one of our staff members tested positive for Covid 19. That staff member was not present at school for the first two days and had no exposure to our students this week.

We worked this afternoon with the Pennsylvania Department of Education and the Department of Health on this situation. Our first priority continues to be the health and safety of our students, staff, and community. Because of this, we are closing school tomorrow, Wednesday, September 2, 2020 out of an overabundance of caution and to make sure we are taking all the necessary steps to ensure everyone's safety.

We will continue to work with our state and local resources tomorrow and thoroughly clean our school building as we have been doing.

We will post resources on our website from the State Department of Health. We will communicate further updates and additional information to our families tomorrow.

Thank you and have a good evening

COME OUT AND SHOW YOUR SUPPORT FOR THE CLASS OF 2020 WITH A "PARADE" to CELEBRATE NEW GRADUATES!!

This Sunday, May 31st the Class of 2020 will be receiving their diplomas, following the diploma ceremony the Salisbury Volunteer Fire Department will be leading the Class of 2020 and their families through town!

The parade should start between 2:45-3:00pm.
Route path:
Leave Salisbury-Elk Lick High School and head up Mechanic St and will make a left onto 219 North.
From there, they will travel to the Boyton Post Office, and back Post Office Road and get back on 219.
The parade will head back into town, and turn right at the light and head down Ord Street towards West Salisbury.
The parade will then heard towards Spings, and will turn around at the Springs church, and head back to Salisbury.

Please feel free to stand outside and show your support for our grads!

post_text:
We missed all the fun activities Mrs. Shafer had planned for Ag Literacy Week 2020, but here's the 2020 Ag Literacy Book, On the Farm, At the Market.
The book highlights a local farmer’s market. It takes readers behind the scenes of the busy market, to three farms where the owners and workers complete the tasks necessary to ensure fresh local produce on market day. All of their efforts culminate in a fresh, locally sourced meal by a chef at a neighborhood restaurant. Reminding us that behind every food we enjoy, at home or at a restaurant, is only possible due to the hard work of farmers throughout the year to grow plants and raise animals.
You can watch Mrs. Shafer read the book on YouTube

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qMbYjJODWok&feature=youtu.be

Pictures can be paid for online at mylifetouch.com, be sure to have your Portrait ID & Access Code (they are on the half sheet in your picture packet). You can also mail your payment to the school at SELSD PO Box 68 Salisbury PA 15558 – Make sure your check is made payable to LIFETOUCH and to return the payment envelope provided by Lifetouch. If you have any questions, please feel free to email me at millert@selsd.com.
High School pictures will be going out on the next student packet pick up.
Thanks,
Toshia Miller, High School Secretary

post_text:
Our Ski Club wrapped up their season with one last trip to @seven springs a few weeks ago!
Special thanks to Share Winter Foundation for the grant we received this year! Students were able to enjoy one of the best ski resorts on the east coast, that also happens to be in our own backyard. All students had a blast and are looking forward to next season!
#sharewinter
#7springs

A note to any SELSD parent - trying to make sure that all our parent emails and phone numbers are up-to-date. Please be sure to email me at millert@selsd.com with your name and current email address and phone number. I know high school teachers will be contacting parents as a way to keep in touch through this new way of learning for our students.

I am happy to make changes to any and all parent emails and phone numbers that need to be changed (elementary & high school) and will pass it along to all of our staff, so they have the updated information.

Thanks! Toshia Miller - High School Secretary

post_text:
The Salisbury-Elk Lick School District sent in an application for approval to provide student lunches during the Governor’s statewide directed closure of schools. The meals would be available at designated pick up places - the former doctor's office in Salisbury, Assembly of God Church in Boynton, St. Paul Wilhelm Church in St. Paul and Springs Mennonite Church.

We are hoping to receive approval by today.

In order to prepare for this, we are asking families if they are interested in receiving meals for your school age child, preK-12th grade. If you are interested please call either the elementary or high school office today to let the secretaries know. They will be taking calls from 8AM to 2PM - please note any food allergies.

Pick up will be from 12 - 12:30.

post_text:
The Salisbury-Elk Lick School District, in compliance with Governor Wolf’s directive late this afternoon, will be closed for the next 10 business days.

All school activities are cancelled or postponed for the next two weeks.

Essential personnel will be working during this period and Administration will be closely monitoring the situation.

We will do our best to communicate updates to our school community as we receive information. We will use our One Call Now system, as well as, our school website and Facebook page for these communications.

The Fitness Club and Athletic Department are sponsoring a stuffed animal toss at the Jr High basketball game Thursday night, 1/16/20 and at the Varsity basketball game on Friday night, 1/17/20.

Anyone bringing a NEW stuffed animal to toss onto the court during the designated time will get into the game for free.

The new stuffed animals will be donated to the Conemaugh-Meyersdale Family Health Care.

Today we hosted our annual Veterans Day Program with guest speaker Sergeant Danielle Girard. After our program our Veterans and their guests were treated Thanksgiving dinner prepared by the Nutrition Group.

Sergeant Girard is pictured by the SELSD sign outside of the high school.

Sergeant Girard is pictured with the 5th grade class.

A group photo of our Veterans and Auxiliary members that were able to join us for our program today.
